rComments: I was never bored during her classes and she was very kind in helping me with coursework. She seems to really care and "gets" being a student. A gem at uoft.

She has a very ideological worldview wherein everything that does not align with it, is considered morally wrong. Nothing short of propaganda for the grievance studies fields. She clearly emphasizes that this course is not scientifically driven, just theory driven (unsupported theories too). She praises Marx and would love to indoctrinate you.
she's a good person. class can be boring but she's very passionate. the only decent prof i had this year.

Her lectures are really boring. She pretty much reads exactly what is shown on the screen and as logn as you did the textbook readings you'll understand her lecture slides. The TA helps to explain things better to us than the prof. Lots of memorization.
Great prof! This course will be a breeze as long as you read the textbook and memorize the lec slides (which are very detailed). As long as you put in the effort, you can easily do very well.

Prof Sicchia is super knowledgeable and passionate. Her slides contain everything that you will need to know but it may be heavy for one lecture. She is truly passionate and makes you interested in the topic! She is one of the best profs at UTSC!! Will def take more courses with her!
Lectures are very dense and full of information, there's a good chance you'll fall asleep since she talks too much. The textbooks are useless but it's good to have them for tutorials
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Insane amount of content in each lecture. Also, she rarely varies what she's saying from what's typed on the slides, which is always paragraphs. Find it pointless to go to lecture. Ended up dropping the second half of this course.. Readings are important to keep up with though. Final paper was too broad for my liking as well

Really recommend going to all of the lectures because that's where most of the content for exams comes from. Sicchia is a great lecturer and makes the material really interesting. The course in itself is not easy/a bird course but if you study the readings and go to lectures, there shouldn't be any surprises on exams!

Great professor! Tells you exactly what to focus on and study for exams and what to expect for assignments. Attending lectures is really important because she adds things that are not on the posted slides. Interesting course, fair marking, Sicchia makes lectures fun + relatable.
Way too much info in one lecture
Most inspirational and caring professor I've ever met!

Very caring prof, concerned that students understand material and can apply it. Syllabus and expectations are very clear. Highly recommend doing the assigned reading and taking notes before lecture due to breadth of info. Provides tips during lecture so attendance is advised. Lectures&txtbks interesting. Tutorials are useful. Marking is fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Amazing course and professor! Every lecture was very interesting and thoughtful! If you follow the instructions for the assignments and exams, you can do well in the class. The teaching team is very helpful :)

It's impossible to not respect and enjoy her lectures and teaching style, as this is the only lecture I refuse to miss. Very engaging and has designed the course in a way where many resources are available in order for students to do well. Wish she would teach more health courses in the future, but hopefully there are more profs like her ;)

Great prof who really cares about her students and about what she's teaching. Very engaging during lectures and she tries to make them interesting even though it is very content heavy. The essays are graded tough by the TAs but I enjoyed tutorials and learned a lot. If you have an interest in health studies I would recommend the course.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: She is a very helpful professor and it's obvious that she is passionate about health. This course is a seminar, so she doesn't lecture as much, rather we do class activities, which is great for a change. However, there are way too many assignments for this one course, and she marks extremely hard. If you don't like writing, avoid this course!!

Very interesting course if you are interested in topics related to health! Dr. Sicchia is a very great prof who is passionate in what she teaches. She makes the class interesting and engaging and is a very strong speaker. The TA's are hard markers for this course but by using office hours and extra help, it is possible to do well in this course!

Overall great course, the only downside is that the TA's are very hard markers when it comes to essays and small assignments. My assignment marks came out average and they stress that you seek outside help when doing the work.  The prof is super sweet and engaging though
really great prof. amazing at saving your grades

Very hard for a first year class HLTA02. The first assignment required students to read 5 academic papers of length such as 9 to 13 pages minimum with size 9 font, horrendous.  Interesting lectures but Suzanne acts like its the best class in the world, believes in her opinion mostly.

Professor Sicchia seems like an incredible person who has a lot of respect for all disciplines of study. Interesting but hard course in the sense that there are a lot of readings. Teaches you how to think critically, pray that you get a good TA for tutorials. For a first year course it can be difficult sometimes.
Very passionate professor, and the work is not as hard as people may say.  Edit, proofread, and do exactly what the instructions say, pay attention to lecture slides & you will do well.
Answers questions, but is a very hard marker. Instructions for assignments are very vague. Too hard for a first year class.
She is an amazing professor. She is very passionate about the content she teaches. Makes you think critically. Loved her class. I would highly recommend it.

Strict, but fair. Hard marker. Very very helpful. If you have any questions, she is always available right after lecture. If she ran out of time, post your question on the discussion board. So far, I've seen every question answered. Follow a "if you give respect, you get respect" rule in her class, and you will do just fine.
Hard-marker when it comes to assignments.
